<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-warning" title="Warning"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Check order referrers carefully</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Pay close attention to activate <strong>ALL</strong> POS order referrers for which the POS user should be able to carry out checkout activities, such as ringing up customers. If, for example, two POS are used in your store, activate both POS order referrers for the user. If you don’t do so, the user will not be able to ring up a customer at POS 1 and later process a return for the same order using POS 2.
If you offer <a href="/en/pos/integrating-plentymarkets-pos#4100">Click &amp; Collect</a> in your online store, you also have to activate the order referrers <strong>Manual entry</strong>, <strong>Client (store)</strong>, and, if used, the specific order referrer for the market used for processing Click &amp; Collect orders.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
