<h2 id="2100">12. Gift cards and promotional coupons</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In plentymarkets, <em>gift cards</em> are treated as a product that customers can buy. If someone has a gift card, then they can redeem it in exchange for products or services.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In contrast, promotional coupons are used for <em>advertising purposes</em>. If someone has a coupon, then they can redeem it to get a discount in your store, e.g. 20% off everything except garden supplies.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Even though gift cards and coupons are used for different things, they are both configured the same way in plentymarkets. Therefore, both topics are explained here in the same chapter.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The following preparations in the plentymarkets back end are necessary to sell gift cards via plentyPOS:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/orders/coupons#15">Decide which items</a> customers should be allowed to purchase with gift cards and coupons.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/orders/coupons#120">Create gift card items</a> with 0% VAT, e.g. add the gift cards to the products that your business sells.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/orders/coupons#20">Create a campaign</a> for your gift cards. Use the option <strong>Coupon variety</strong> to specifiy whether it is a gift card or a promotional coupon.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/orders/coupons#130">link your gift card items with the campaign</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Optional:</em></strong> <a href="/en/pos/integrating-plentymarkets-pos#850">Generate codes</a> or save your own coupon codes in the back end.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Optional:</em></strong> Create gift card templates and make them available to POS users.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Optional:</em></strong> Make gift card codes available to POS users.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock note">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-note" title="Note"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">More than one POS</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Do you have more than one POS and create your own gift card codes? Divide the printed gift card codes between the different POS or create a separate gift card campaign and gift card items to make sure that each gift card code is sold only once.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="830">12.1. Creating a campaign for POS gift cards</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Now, create one or several campaigns for selling gift cards in plentyPOS. You have the following options:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>You create one campaign for all gift cards you sell in plentyPOS.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>You create one campaign for each gift card value.<br>
*<em>Example:</em>*You want to sell gift cards for 10 GBP, 25 GBP and 50 GBP and a gift card with a flexible value that POS users enter during the transaction. As such, you create 3 campaigns with the discount values 10, 25 and 50 GBP and a campaign with an amount of your choice.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you operate more than one POS and want to use your own gift card codes it also may make sense to create separate campaigns for each POS. Proceed as described below to create a campaign for gift cards:</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a campaign for POS gift cards:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Orders » Coupons</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>New campaign</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings. Note <a href="#table-POS-gift-card-campaigns">Table 14</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The new campaign is created and appears in the overview.</p>
</li>
</ol>
