<h2 id="960">22. Changing POS orders in the plentymarkets back end</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>An order is created for POS orders in the plentymarkets back end. After the order has been created, legally relevant order details can no longer be changed. Only order details that change in the course of processing and fulfilling orders or that document the order history can be changed:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Language</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Status</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Amount paid</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Payment status</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Reasons for return</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Assign order to a multi-order</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Delivery address</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Emailing</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Order note</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Shipped on</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Return date</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
